1
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,280
You are now my junior officially.

2
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,400
If any of us have problems

3
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:11,040
we will help each other.

4
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:12,480
You are so smart, P’Kongpob.

5
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:14,400
I and Khaofang are stuck.

6
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:15,680
Actually, it’s not difficult

7
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:18,080
You just need to adopt this formula in order to solve.

8
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:20,440
Look around and see the smiles on their face

9
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:22,760
It’s not as bad as you think, is it?

10
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,680
Arthit, get me a coffee.

11
00:02:25,040 --> 00:02:25,680
I give you money later.

12
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:26,440
Okay.

13
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:29,520
Don’t get used to being taken advantage at work.

14
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:30,440
Okay

15
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:31,880
Why hadn’t you told me that you would be here?

16
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,640
Why do have to snap at me?

17
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:36,040
Or you don’t want me to be here?

18
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,760
In the future, when you want to come to my room

19
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:43,800
let me know first.

20
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,880
There could be a chance that I’m caught up in a meeting

21
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:50,920
or go out to meet clients

22
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:53,080
And you cannot see me.

23
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,160
I don’t want you to waste time on waiting for me

24
00:02:55,640 --> 00:02:56,640
Okay.

25
00:02:58,120 --> 00:03:00,440
Do you still have work to do today?

26
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,560
No

27
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:03,840
What about you?

28
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:05,240
You come to see me.

29
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,160
Is everything all right?

30
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,040
I want to talk about the initiation

31
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:09,120
But…

32
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:12,920
let’s eat first.

33
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,640
Well, my room is a bit messy.

34
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,600
You come without notice

35
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:21,880
I don’t have time to clean up yet.

36
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:24,760
Let me help.

37
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:06,840
P’Arthit krap.

38
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:11,760
That bottle belongs to me.

39
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:13,720
Why?

40
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,480
There are many drinks in the fridge.

41
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:16,800
Be generous.

42
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:19,240
But there’s only one left of that favor

43
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,160
You want it?

44
00:04:26,960 --> 00:04:28,040
Here.

45
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:48,360
Why is the steamed egg in this color this time?

46
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:50,400
It’s special recipe

47
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,080
How was it?

48
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:00,920
Well…

49
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,640
it’s so-so.

50
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:03,760
Not that special.

51
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:05,720
I put it away then.

52
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:06,760
Wait.

53
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,760
Didn’t you said it was not good?

54
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:19,560
Anyway,

55
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,440
about the off-campus initiation at the beach

56
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:22,800
has it been approved yet?

57
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:25,000
We are only waiting for the authorized letter.

58
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:28,120
The new dean is yet to sign it off.

59
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:30,000
That happens every year.

60
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:31,800
It’s common for the dean.

61
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:33,520
During my time,

62
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,120
the dean didn’t sign off easily

63
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,760
so I had to add other activities to the plan

64
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,400
Other activities…

65
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:41,280
like volunteer camps?

66
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,200
Yes.

67
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,680
In fact, I think...

68
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,960
you could add an activity like a reforestation.

69
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:49,720
I think it’s interesting.

70
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:50,880
Add it to your plan

71
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,120
All right.

72
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:54,000
I’ll try that.

73
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,520
If I get the green light,

74
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:59,800
are you going with me?

75
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,280
Sure.

76
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:04,320
You want me to go with you, right?

77
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:07,480
Let’s finish eating.

78
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,120
But if you are busy with your work,

79
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:10,040
you don’t have to go.

80
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:12,160
I want you to have a deserved rest.

81
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:14,160
I consider that a kind of rest too

82
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,080
I get to meet the juniors

83
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:18,760
and do activities together with them

84
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,160
Okay.

85
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,600
I take that as you have agreed to go

86
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,080
Kongpob

87
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:37,160
what the hell did you do?

88
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:39,160
Take it off

89
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,760
What time is it now, Kongpob?

90
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,520
8 o’clock.

91
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:59,160
Don’t you have class tomorrow?

92
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,600
I do

93
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,400
In the afternoon?

94
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:05,760
Why?

95
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:08,800
Do you want to kick me out now?

96
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,760
No.

97
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,360
Hold on, Kongpob.

98
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,960
What?

99
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:26,440
Don’t tell me that you have planned this from the beginning?

100
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:36,640
You have me fooled again.

101
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,320
Hey!

102
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:41,320
Hey!

103
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,440
Here you go again.

104
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:46,360
Kongpob, this is not funny

105
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:48,160
It’s late. Let me in.

106
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:01,120
You could be late for work

107
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:02,520
Give me 5 more minutes.

108
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,760
No.

109
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:06,240
Get up.

110
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:08,360
What time is it?

111
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,040
It’s 8 o’clock?

112
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,720
What?

113
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:18,240
8 o’clock already?

114
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:21,720
And you didn’t bother to wake me up again

115
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:26,080
That’s your favorite line when you wake up late.

116
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,680
But it’s 8 o’clock.

117
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,200
I’m kidding.

118
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:31,680
It’s just half past 7.

119
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:51,040
What shirt do you want to wear today?

120
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,480
I iron it for you.

121
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,680
Uh…

122
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:55,960
the white one.

123
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:58,000
Any white shirt is fine. Just pick it.

124
00:09:17,160 --> 00:09:19,080
Do you want to eat?

125
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:22,840
I don’t think I have enough time.

126
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,960
Please work hard, P’Arthit.

127
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:52,880
Thank you, Kongpob.

128
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,280
Arthit

129
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:08,400
Yes, P’John.

130
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,360
I have an important matter that needs your favor

131
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,680
I have placed an order from a supplier.

132
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:16,000
I want you to call and chase them for me

133
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,600
Tell them to deliver the order by the end of this month.

134
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:20,840
Okay.

135
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:24,680
Okay. Here are their telephone number and contact person.

136
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:28,320
Don’t forget to remind them that they must deliver by the end of this month

137
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,760
Got it. By the end of this month

138
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,160
Hold on.

139
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:33,920
What?

140
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:34,880
P’John,

141
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:39,160
But it states here that the delivery date is the first Monday of next month.

142
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,760
I know.

143
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:43,000
But it’s too late to get it then

144
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,080
You got it, right?

145
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:44,880
Yes.

146
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,120
Sawasdee krap.

147
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,040
Ah, sawasdee krap.

148
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:56,920
My name is Arthit.

149
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:59,760
I’m calling from the Procurement Department of Ocean Electric Company.

150
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:01,920
May I speak to Khun Supot?

151
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:02,600
Yes, Supot’s speaking.

152
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:03,960
What can I do for you?

153
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:05,240
Well, Khun Supot

154
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:09,480
the purchase order number 0023247

155
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:12,720
Is it possible to have the order by the last Friday of this month instead?

156
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:15,440
Well, Khun Arthit. You can’t rush us.

157
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,960
Actually, when I spoke to Khun John last week,

158
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:20,680
I thought I could get the purchase order right after we talked

159
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,680
Last week?

160
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:23,560
Yes.

161
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:24,960
And I already speed up the production process

162
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:27,040
to have it ready by Monday next month.

163
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:31,120
If that the case, please accept my apologies.

164
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:35,200
But we really need it by the end of this month.

165
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,440
Can you please rush it for me?

166
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,320
All right, Khun Arthit.

167
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:42,320
Since Khun John and I have been working together,

168
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:44,960
I try to finish it on Saturday of the end of this month

169
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:48,240
All right. Saturday is fine.

170
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:49,960
Sorry again that we can’t rush it and deliver it on Friday.

171
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:52,560
It’s okay. Thank you very much

172
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,680
Can they do it?

173
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,080
Well, P’John.

174
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:06,640
Khun Supot said the best he could do is Saturday at the end of this month.

175
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:12,040
Bummer. I’m not available on that day

176
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:14,640
A friend from Beijing will come to see me

177
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,360
So I can’t come to the office.

178
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,160
You have to be here to get it for me then

179
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:21,280
Thank you, Arthit.

180
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,240
Okay. I’ll do it

181
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:36,920
Sawasdee krap, everyone.

182
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:40,080
Sawasdee krap/ka

183
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:42,200
We would like to invite you all

184
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:44,360
to participate in the initiation activity at the beach

185
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:46,320
The last Saturday of this month

186
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:47,960
We guarantee you that it’ll be fun.

187
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:50,080
We are definitely going, P’Oak

188
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,280
Let’s go together, Khaofang.

189
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:56,240
Well, I have to ask my mother for permission.

190
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:57,440
You don’t need to.

191
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:58,560
I used to ask my father too

192
00:12:58,640 --> 00:12:59,640
and he said go ahead.

193
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:01,880
He urged me to go

194
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:05,440
are you sure we can already invite these juniors?

195
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:07,280
We haven’t received the authorization yet.

196
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:08,640
It’s going to be okay.

197
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:10,160
We can find the way somehow.

198
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,520
Trust me.

199
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:14,520
All right then, we are going to be at our usual table

200
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,480
Please help spread the invitation for us.

201
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:18,440
Okay.

202
00:13:21,520 --> 00:13:23,640
May, I bought this for you.

203
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:30,160
what should we do with that Boss.

204
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:33,720
I know you have strong skills.

205
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:35,680
It’s not difficult. You are his senior.

206
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,680
Hey hey, you guys.

207
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:38,720
Don’t worry.

208
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,480
I and Kong will talk to him.

209
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,320
See?

210
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,080
Nong Day,

211
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:56,240
we would like to ask you to join the initiation activity at the beach

212
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:58,520
on the last Saturday of this month.

213
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:00,120
Please join us.

214
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:03,440
In this upcoming initiation activity

215
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:05,240
I want everyone to go there and enjoy

216
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,120
including you

217
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,000
All of us, seniors

218
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:08,840
and your friends

219
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:10,680
would like you to join.

220
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,160
Thank you.

221
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:13,760
But…

222
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:15,720
please excuse me.

223
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:17,280
Why?

224
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:19,160
Well,

225
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:21,440
other students have the right to go

226
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:24,640
I also have the right to not go.

227
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:28,280
But most of them go.

228
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:30,760
Most of them?

229
00:14:30,920 --> 00:14:33,320
How do you measure it?

230
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:09,120
How many names have you got, Kong?

231
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:11,600
200 names.

232
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:12,840
What about you, M?

233
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,520
I’ve got 150 names.

234
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:16,480
I’ve got 150 names too.

235
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,360
So, we’ve reached the target.

236
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:18,840
Yeah.

237
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:19,440
Really?

238
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:21,200
You’ve got 150?

239
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:22,040
Yeah.

240
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:23,240
Hey, that’s done.

241
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:25,160
We’ve got 500 names already.

242
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,520
Sweet!

243
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:29,040
Excuse me.

244
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:31,960
Sawasdee krap.

245
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:33,000
Sawasdee krap.

246
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:35,040
What’s the matter, Khun Kongpob?

247
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:37,640
I would like to talk to you about the initiation.

248
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:40,120
I have given you my answer.

249
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:42,760
Can you please look at this document once again?

250
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:47,680
The is the name list of students who want to participate in the activity.

251
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:51,520
May I ask you to reconsider it?

252
00:15:54,680 --> 00:15:58,200
I promise that I won’t do anything that risks damaging the university’s reputation

253
00:16:50,920 --> 00:16:52,800
Receiving products BN, plastic

254
00:16:58,680 --> 00:16:59,520
What’s up?

255
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:00,840
What are you doing?

256
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:02,280
Have you eaten?

257
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:04,760
I’m about to eat the steamed egg you made.

258
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:06,760
Please enjoy it.

259
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:10,240
On the last Saturday of this month

260
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,280
we have the initiation activity

261
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:14,280
I just got the green light this afternoon today.

262
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:16,240
Please go with me.

263
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:23,800
Kongpob, I’m sorry but I have to go to the office that day.

264
00:17:24,080 --> 00:17:26,240
I have to cover for a senior colleague.

265
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:28,520
I already give him my word that I would help

266
00:17:29,280 --> 00:17:31,040
It’s all right.

267
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:48,600
“Engineering Volunteer Camp
Let’s Grow Trees”

268
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:50,880
Are you sure you don’t want to join us?

269
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:52,120
No.

270
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:55,920
We may think differently.

271
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:58,200
But I have learned a lot from you.

272
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,320
Thank you.

273
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:11,400
0058

274
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:16,160
You don’t have to convince me.

275
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:21,640
Don’t drag me to grow trees with you.

276
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:24,600
I can call the police to arrest you for abduction attempt.

277
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:26,440
Okay.

278
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:28,920
I’m not here to force anything.

279
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:32,160
0058, I just want to tell you

280
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:34,000
if you change your mind

