566
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:09,000
And I can apply again.

567
00:36:09,120 --> 00:36:10,480
Really, P’Arthit.

568
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:11,800
You have already been employed by a big company.

569
00:36:12,080 --> 00:36:12,840
Why are you still being picky?

570
00:36:13,240 --> 00:36:14,040
If I were you,

571
00:36:14,160 --> 00:36:15,640
I would be happy to work with any department they want

572
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:17,320
Well, here’s the thing.

573
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:19,560
When you graduate and enter the world of working

574
00:36:19,960 --> 00:36:23,320
you will see that the world outside

575
00:36:23,680 --> 00:36:25,800
is totally different than what we have on the campus

576
00:36:26,240 --> 00:36:27,400
There is pressure

577
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:29,440
Everything has its own system and process

578
00:36:29,720 --> 00:36:32,560
Look, I have to get up early to carry on my work.

579
00:36:34,160 --> 00:36:34,920
Listen,

580
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:37,520
when you have to do the internship

581
00:36:37,640 --> 00:36:39,800
you know what it’s like out there.

582
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:41,480
Do you understand?

583
00:36:42,240 --> 00:36:43,240
Yes, sir.

584
00:36:43,600 --> 00:36:45,920
After hearing that, I don’t want to graduate now

585
00:36:46,120 --> 00:36:48,920
Yes, you don’t need to hurriedly graduate.

586
00:36:49,320 --> 00:36:50,240
Look at me.

587
00:36:50,560 --> 00:36:52,160
I graduated but I’m still unemployed.

588
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:56,400
That’s not the case.

589
00:36:56,520 --> 00:36:58,280
It’s not that you don’t have job to do.

590
00:36:58,360 --> 00:36:59,400
You just don’t bother to look for it.

591
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:00,560
No, I do look for it.

592
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:01,880
Have you found any job to do?

593
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:02,640
Yes,

594
00:37:02,720 --> 00:37:03,880
I found one job.

595
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:05,560
What job?

596
00:37:05,600 --> 00:37:07,880
I think you like this job too, Bright

597
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:10,000
Really? What is it?

598
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:13,960
A photographer for pretty female models at the Motor Show.

599
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:23,360
P’Arthit krap,

600
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:26,160
when you arrive Bangkok

601
00:37:26,760 --> 00:37:27,920
can you text me?

602
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:30,760
Sure.

603
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:32,560
Don’t worry.

604
00:37:32,800 --> 00:37:34,800
Bright has slept off for a long time.

605
00:37:35,520 --> 00:37:36,760
We are going to be safe.

606
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:42,520
Are you going now?

607
00:37:43,680 --> 00:37:45,800
Yes, I should.

608
00:37:46,240 --> 00:37:47,720
I’ll see you again.

609
00:37:50,280 --> 00:37:51,920
Okay.

610
00:38:12,640 --> 00:38:13,640
Kong…

611
00:38:27,080 --> 00:38:29,040
That’s your reward.

612
00:38:35,400 --> 00:38:36,840
I think…

613
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:41,440
that’s the reward for being the head hazer

614
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:46,760
What about the reward of being your boyfriend?

615
00:38:51,760 --> 00:38:53,280
Get it later.

616
00:38:56,440 --> 00:38:57,760
P’Arthit!

617
00:39:06,040 --> 00:39:09,800
Directed by
Padung Smajarn / Pongpisit Botsri

618
00:39:33,680 --> 00:39:35,200
You can play basketball too, P’Arthit?

619
00:39:35,440 --> 00:39:36,800
Just a little bit.

620
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:39,320
How about a three-point shootout?

621
00:39:39,560 --> 00:39:40,440
Why not?

622
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:42,680
I have one condition

623
00:39:42,800 --> 00:39:43,720
Which is…

624
00:39:44,400 --> 00:39:46,040
It’s not fun if we compete without something at stake.

625
00:39:46,520 --> 00:39:48,480
If I can make a three-point field goal,

626
00:39:49,160 --> 00:39:50,800
you will let me kiss your cheek.

627
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:52,960
But if you can make a three-point field goal,

628
00:39:53,720 --> 00:39:54,600
I will let you kiss mine.

629
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:55,680
What?

630
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:57,000
No.

631
00:39:57,240 --> 00:39:59,400
I’m at a disadvantage

632
00:39:59,760 --> 00:40:00,720
How about this?

633
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:01,880
If you can make a three-point field goal

634
00:40:02,080 --> 00:40:03,400
I will let you kiss my cheek.

635
00:40:03,680 --> 00:40:05,120
But if I can make a three-point field goal,

636
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,600
you must do 5 push-ups each

637
00:40:08,320 --> 00:40:10,480
I’ll pull my punches for you.

638
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:26,080
If you can’t put it in the hoop,

639
00:40:26,080 --> 00:40:27,880
I’ll kiss your cheek.

640
00:40:58,640 --> 00:40:59,640
1

641
00:40:59,680 --> 00:41:00,640
2

642
00:41:00,640 --> 00:41:01,560
3

643
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:02,560
4

644
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:03,520
5

645
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:09,520
I’m not pulling my punches now

646
00:41:09,520 --> 00:41:10,560
Okay.

647
00:41:49,120 --> 00:41:49,920
Hi.

648
00:41:50,120 --> 00:41:51,680
Sawasdee krap, P’Rock.

649
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:53,480
What are you playing? Can I join?

650
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:55,280
We are doing a three-point shootout

651
00:41:55,440 --> 00:41:56,920
Do you want to join?

652
00:41:57,160 --> 00:41:58,560
Three-point shootout?

653
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:02,000
Arthit was the winner of the three-point contest

654
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:04,080
I better go play that side.

655
00:42:06,280 --> 00:42:07,640
So?

656
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:08,800
Do you want to continue?

657
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:10,160
You can’t be serious

658
00:42:12,760 --> 00:42:14,120
How about we play football?

659
00:42:17,080 --> 00:42:17,440
What?

660
00:42:17,680 --> 00:42:18,680
Football?

661
00:42:18,760 --> 00:42:20,040
Not in the mood yet.

662
00:42:26,760 --> 00:42:35,520
“Find a good moment and confess your feelings to her. Maybe..
